#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/position.xml.1.chaine:100-1000
#, 
msgid "The /usr Versus /usr/local Debate"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/position.xml.1.chaine:100-1001
#, 
msgid "Should I install XXX in _F845_ or _F846_ ?"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/position.xml.1.chaine:100-1002
#, 
msgid "This is a question without an obvious answer for an LFS based system."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/position.xml.1.chaine:100-1003
#, 
msgid "In traditional Unix systems, _F190_ usually contains files that come with the system distribution, and the _F268_ tree is free for the local administrator to manage."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/position.xml.1.chaine:100-1004
#, 
msgid "The only really hard and fast rule is that Unix distributions should not touch _F268_ , except perhaps to create the basic directories within it."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/position.xml.1.chaine:100-1005
#, 
msgid "With Linux distributions like Red Hat, Debian, etc., a possible rule is that _F190_ is managed by the distribution's package system and _F268_ is not."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/position.xml.1.chaine:100-1006
#, 
msgid "This way the package manager's database knows about every file within _F190_ ."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/position.xml.1.chaine:100-1007
#, 
msgid "LFS users build their own system and so deciding where the system ends and local files begin is not straightforward."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/position.xml.1.chaine:100-1008
#, 
msgid "So the choice should be made in order to make things easier to administer."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/position.xml.1.chaine:100-1009
#, 
msgid "There are several reasons for dividing files between _F190_ and _F268_ ."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/position.xml.1.chaine:100-1010
#, 
msgid "On a network of several machines all running LFS, or mixed LFS and other Linux distributions, _F268_ could be used to hold packages that are common between all the computers in the network."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/position.xml.1.chaine:100-1011
#, 
msgid "It can be NFS mounted or mirrored from a single server."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/position.xml.1.chaine:100-1012
#, 
msgid "Here local indicates local to the site."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/position.xml.1.chaine:100-1013
#, 
msgid "On a network of several computers all running an identical LFS system, _F268_ could hold packages that are different between the machines."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/position.xml.1.chaine:100-1014
#, 
msgid "In this case local refers to the individual computers."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/position.xml.1.chaine:100-1015
#, 
msgid "Even on a single computer, _F268_ can be useful if you have several distributions installed simultaneously, and want a place to put packages that will be the same on all of them."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/position.xml.1.chaine:100-1016
#, 
msgid "Or you might regularly rebuild your LFS, but want a place to put files that you don't want to rebuild each time."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/position.xml.1.chaine:100-1017
#, 
msgid "This way you can wipe the LFS file system and start from a clean partition every time without losing everything."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/position.xml.1.chaine:100-1018
#, 
msgid "Some people ask why not use your own directory tree, e.g., _F847_ , rather than _F268_ ?"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/position.xml.1.chaine:100-1019
#, 
msgid "There is nothing stopping you, many sites do make their own trees, however it makes installing new software more difficult."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/position.xml.1.chaine:100-1020
#, 
msgid "Automatic installers often look for dependencies in _F190_ and _F268_ , and if the file it is looking for is in _F847_ instead, the installer will probably fail unless you specifically tell it where to look."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/position.xml.1.chaine:100-1021
#, 
msgid "What is the BLFS position on this?"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/position.xml.1.chaine:100-1022
#, 
msgid "All of the BLFS instructions install programs in _F190_ with optional instructions to install into _F685_ for some specific packages."
msgstr ""

